  "text": "Acoustic holography is an advanced technology for sound source identification and sound field visualization. Williams and Maynard put forward the generalized theory of acoustic holography in 1980s [CITATION_1] . The technique requires holographic data to be measured in the near-field of the sound source, so it is also called near-field acoustical holography (NAH). Since this method based on two-dimensional spatial Fourier transform is mainly applied to regular measurement surfaces, it has limitations in engineering applications.",
